	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />DSi mode is controlled by a digital signing key that only Nintendo has. There are a couple save-game exploits to get into DSi mode, but the PXI calls to get to the SD card to load more code aren't cracked yet.
<br />
<br />And the CPU is only twice as fast, which by itself won't help Lynx get 100%. GP2X family (or Pandora if they ever figure out how to build them faster) might be the best option in this case.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


